[2]
Date: Tue 8 Dec 2020 19:23 IST
Source: The Indian Express [edited]
https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/hyderabad/andhra-pradesh-eluru-mysterious-disease-aiims-report-lead-nickel-heavy-metals-7096843/


A preliminary report of All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS), Delhi, has found traces of heavy metals lead and nickel in at least 10 blood samples collected from patients from different places in Eluru town in West Godavari District in Andhra Pradesh. The AIIMS team conducted the blood tests after at least 550 people fell sick in Eluru town since Saturday evening [5 Dec 2020] due to an undiagnosed illness. The results indicate lead and nickel content in drinking water or/and milk as the possible reason behind people falling ill. [This is confusing. The blood tests indicate possible lead and nickel. A blood test cannot tell the source of the metals. So how did they jump to water and/or milk? There is no indication the water has been tested nor is there indication any milk source has been tested. - Mod.TG]

Superintendent of Eluru Government Hospital Dr. AV Mohan told The Indian Express: "The sample size we sent on an urgent basis to AIIMS was small, but their report indicates presence of heavy metals like lead and nickel in the blood samples of patients. We have sent more samples and their reports are awaited."

Dr. Mohan said of the 550 people who were admitted, only 84 remain in hospitals now and they would also be discharged soon.

[Byline: Sreenivas Janyala]

