[So bacterial and viral conditions have been ruled out. The focus seems to be on some heavy metal contamination, likely lead and nickel. However, water and food do not seem to be the source, according to this article.

While heavy metals may cause neurological signs, at this point in the investigation it is difficult to comment if all the individuals tested had elevated lead and nickel or if other metals are involved. It is also difficult to comment on the possible sources, as some seem to have been ruled out, but testing is ongoing.

Generally, heavy metal toxicity does not strike so many so suddenly unless the level is extremely high, and all are exposed at the same time. So this is still odd. - Mod.TG]

[Andhra Pradesh is a state in the southeastern coastal region of India. Eluru is a city and the district headquarters of West Godavari district (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eluru). West Godavari is one of the 9 districts in its coastal region of Andhra Pradesh (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coastal_Andhra). A map showing the location of the districts of Andhra Pradesh can be found at https://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/andhrapradesh/andhrapradesh-district.htm.

ProMED-mail would appreciate more information on this outbreak from knowledgeable sources. - Mod.ML

